Eight people were killed when a fire broke out in the Taiwan informal settlement in Khayelitsha in Cape Town. The City of Cape Town Fire and Rescue Services says the incident happened in the early hours of Monday morning. It's reported that four shacks were destroyed by the fire which left 22 people homeless. Allegedly two women, two men, three boys and one girl died in the fire. The cause of the incident is still unclear at the moment, but it's being investigated. 